comment._content: en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Olecko indicates that "Marggrabowa was founded as a town by Albert of Brandenburg-Ansbach, Duke of the Duchy of Prussia, on January 1, 1560. The town's Masurian Slavic-sounding name is derived from the German word Markgraf, the duke's title as the margraviate of Brandenburg's prince. " The city is currently in Poland and known as Olecko. See www.um.olecko.pl/
